title: Velocity Calculation
text: Use the formula: v=2*a*s​, where v is the final velocity, a is the acceleration due to gravity $$(9.80$$ $$\frac{m}{s^2}$$ downward in this case), and s is the displacement $$(3.0$$ $$m$$ in this case).

title: Velocity Calculation
text: Substitute the given values into the formula v=2*a*s​ to find the velocity v.
